<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing -
        Installation - Flexplate (Automatic Transmissions)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="4">
        <title>Flexplate (Automatic Transmissions)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Allison 2000 Series Transmissions</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, if the vehicle is being reconfigured with an Allison 2000 Series
                        transmission, make sure that the correct flywheel housing is installed on the engine. Otherwise,
                        there will be interference between the flexplate studs and the flywheel housing that will only
                        be evident after the transmission has been installed.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2651332" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH07/H07006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing guide pins and adapter hub</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Adapter hub</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Guide pins</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two guide pins in the flexplate mounting bolt holes at the 3 o'clock and 9
                    o'clock positions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the adapter hub on the guide pins.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651333" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH07/H07008.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the flexplate</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Flexplate assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When installed correctly, the ring gear on the flexplate is offset (not centered) toward the
                        transmission.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the flexplate assembly on the guide pins.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, make sure the reinforcement ring is installed with the paint mark or
                        XMSN SIDE facing outward (towards the transmission), otherwise, premature flexplate failure may
                        occur.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2651334" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH07/H07007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing reinforcement ring with paint mark</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the reinforcement ring on the guide pins (made locally) with paint mark facing
                    outward.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install ten flexplate mounting bolts finger tight.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the guide pins and install the remaining two flexplate mounting bolts finger
                    tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the flexplate mounting bolts to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_268.xml" xrefid="t13002" appearance="hottext">special torque
                        value</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>MD-3000 and HD-4000 Series World Transmissions</title>
            <figure id="f2651335" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8971.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the flexplate assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Flexplate assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">End of crankshaft</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two guide pins in the flexplate mounting bolt holes at the 3 o'clock and 9
                    o'clock positions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The flexplate assembly is available as a completely assembled service part.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the flexplate assembly on the guide pins.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This following step applies to MD transmissions only.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install reinforcement ring with part number or logo facing outward (towards the
                    transmission).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install ten flexplate mounting bolts finger tight.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the guide pins and install the remaining two flexplate mounting bolts finger
                    tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the flexplate mounting bolts to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_268.xml" xrefid="t13002" appearance="hottext">special torque
                        value</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Flywheel and ring gear are part of the torque converter assembly.</para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>Make sure that the paint mark, part number or XMSN SIDE on the flexplate is facing outward
                        (towards the transmission).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
    <spec>
